comments.body:
Right the scenario I'm describing is leveraging the same original issue from #8279, just concerning censorship of a non-upgraded initial sender.

```
               // Note, any on-top-of-base-layer software (eg LN-node) relying on a non-upgraded to wtxid-relay full-node 
              //  would be subject to censor of its time-sensitive transactions. See https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18044#discussion_r443419034
             //  Removing this restriction should be done considering ecosystem coordination.
```

I think "broadly" is to dim, ideally you want 99% of upgrade among LN-node's full-nodes.

