comments.body:
FWIW, I think `mempool.exists(hash, by_wtxid)` is more convenient/readable in AlreadyHave (the only place `wtxid_exists()` is used); it would let you say:

```
    const bool by_wtxid = (inv.type == MSG_WTX); 
    return mempool.exists(inv.hash, by_wtxid));
```

instead of

```
    return (inv.type != MSG_WTX && mempool.exists(inv.hash)) ||
           (inv.type == MSG_WTX && mempool.wtxid_exists(inv.hash));
```

